  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Construction Supervisor",
  "description": "<p>a. Supervise and manage of construction workers on daily site activities.</p>\n<p>b. Keep track of the site schedule to ensure works are on time.</p>\n<p>c. Compliance to safe work procedures and maintain good house-keeping.</p>\n<p>d. Ensure safety matters on site and quality of completed works.</p>\n<p>e. Check and ensure material order and fabrication works in compliance with the specification and drawings.</p>\n<p>f. Responsible for the day to day supervision of projects and carry out associated administrative duties.</p>\n<p>g. Monitor employee productivity and provide constructive feedback and coaching</p>\n<p>h. Ensure quality construction standards and the use of proper construction techniques.</p>\n<p>i. Maintain timekeeping and personnel records.</p>\n<p>j. Pass on information from upper management to employees and vice-versa.</p>\n<p>k. Ensure adherence to legal and company policies and procedures and undertake disciplinary actions if the need arises.</p>\n<p><strong>Working conditions</strong></p>\n<p>Due to the nature of the job, there might be requirements for regular overtime work, weekend works and working with challenging client.</p>\n<p><strong>Requirement</strong></p>\n<p>·At least 1 years’ reinforced concrete works experience in construction is required.(Experience in formwork or carpentry is preferred)</p>",
